BR_text.BRsummary: Backend test runner doesn't honor SequenceProto inputs/outputs
BR_text.BRdescription:
<denchmark-h:h1>Bug Report</denchmark-h>
 
 Noticed that the onnx backend test runner doesn't have logic <denchmark-link:https://github.com/onnx/onnx/blob/5cc790e03b2af691c55926a11c116eb9edaa689b/onnx/backend/test/runner/__init__.py#L298>in place</denchmark-link>
  to handle s in the model's test inputs/outputs. Currently, it assumes that everything is a TensorProto. There are exisitng node tests that use sequences as inputs/outputs (for example: if_seq, loop13_seq, sequence_insert_at_front, sequence_insert_at_back) that is unable to be handled by the runner.
 This change added support for s : <denchmark-link:https://github.com/onnx/onnx/pull/2581>#2581</denchmark-link>
